    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-07-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-07-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="183"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d183">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Abbott</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Bogota</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-07-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 18, 1890</date>. (Received August
                        19.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 95.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I acknowledge the receipt of your instruction No.
                    67 of May 29 last, in which you direct me to maintain the validity of the acts
                    of Consul Vifquain in the matter of the Smith estate in Colon.</p>
                <p>Dr. Roldàn informed me this morning, himself introducing the subject, that he
                    would discuss the matter with me as soon as possible, probably within 3 weeks,
                    and that he thought, we should have no difficulty in coming to an
                    understanding.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John T. Abbott.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
